@startuml deletePost
!include ../../theme/theme-dark-seq.puml
title deletePost flow
actor User
participant Resolver
participant PostsService as P
participant LikesService as L
database DB

User -> Resolver: deletePost()
Resolver -> P: deletePost() : bool

group postsRepo.manager.transaction
  P -> DB: lockEntityByIdOrThrow(Post) + load user relation
  DB --> P: post

  P -> P: validate ownership

  P -> DB: lockCommentIdsForPost()
  DB --> P: commentIds

  P -> L: deleteLikes()
  L -> DB: repo.delete() [post likes]
  DB --> L: ok
  L --> P: ok

  P -> L: deleteLikes()
  L -> DB: repo.delete() [comment likes]
  DB --> L: ok
  L --> P: ok

  P -> DB: manager.remove(Post)

  note over L,DB
  FK cascade rules handle dependent deletes:
  - post deletion triggers deleting its comments
  - post deletion triggers deleting its and its like activities
  - comment deletion triggers deleting its and its like activities
  end note

  par post-delete cascades
    par 
      DB -> DB: CASCADE delete post activities
    else 
      DB -> DB: CASCADE delete post-like activities
    end
  else comment-delete cascades
    DB -> DB: CASCADE delete comments
    par 
      DB -> DB: CASCADE delete comment activities
    else 
      DB -> DB: CASCADE delete comment-like activities
    end
  end

  DB --> P: post deleted
end

P --> Resolver: true
Resolver --> User: data.deletePost = true

== Error rule ==
note over P,DB
If any awaited step inside the transaction throws:
TypeORM issues ROLLBACK, then error bubbles to resolver,
and resolver returns a GraphQL error.
end note
@enduml
